  "text": "At present, we consider that enhancement of brain glucose uptake is an effect of the presence of BMSCs into subarachnoid space and its subsequent diffusion to the whole brain by cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) [CITATION_1] . In our present case report we have studied the new foci of metabolic activity at Th12 and L1 vertebral level ( Figure 2D) , and persisted the enhancement in brain metabolism. One year after the end of cell therapy, the pattern of glucose uptake was considered normal in the brain, without foci of hypermetabolism into spinal canal.",
